
Overview of noun plight

The noun plight has 2 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (8) predicament, quandary, plight -- (a situation from which extrication is difficult especially an unpleasant or trying one; "finds himself in a most awkward predicament"; "the woeful plight of homeless people")
2. plight, troth -- (a solemn pledge of fidelity)

